title: Times-Union staff predictions: Jaguars at Buccaneers
text:
Times-Union staff predictions: Jaguars at Buccaneers 
By Times-Union Sat, Oct 10, 2015 @ 9:02 pm | updated Sat, Oct 10, 2015 @ 9:18 pm 
Hays Carlyon: JAGUARS 28, BUCCANEERS 20 
The high yardage totals for Blake Bortles and Co. will result in touchdowns against Tampa Bay. The defense will get a couple of turnovers off Jameis Winston to secure the victory. 
Ryan O'Halloran: BUCCANEERS 31, JAGUARS 27 
Playing at home means Tampa Bay needs this game more than the Jaguars need it. Jameis Winston will rebound from his five-turnover debacle last week to drop the Jaguars to 1-4. 
Vito Stellino: JAGUARS 17, BUCCANEERS 16 
Blake Bortles showed he has leadership skills when he said a quarterback has to will his team to victory. He will make the big plays to do that Sunday against a struggling Bucs team.
